  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nSupport `convert(a, Bytes[N])` for `a:bytesM`.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nIt is more straightforward to read and understand than `concat(b\"\", a)`, which is what is required at present. \r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nSince both types are right-padded, the conversion should be a no-op (i.e. type system only). Except we must check `M <= N` or revert. Equivalently (I hope) it is the inverse of `convert(b, bytesM)` for `b:Bytes[N]`.\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNew feature: no incompatibility. Previously would not typecheck.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n## References\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
